  "narrative": "3.125(a) \n   \nFacilities, general. \nThe wooden shade structure in the Guinea Hog enclosure has 2 solid sides and 2 open sides. One of the open sides had \na pair of boards at ground level for the threshold. The outermost board had partially detached from the threshold resulting \nin a gap approximately 1 inch wide, and approximately 1/3 of the top edge of the outermost board had broken off. \n \nPer this Section, outdoor housing facilities shall be maintained in good repair to protect the animals from injury. The \npartially detached/damaged board along the shade structure\u2019s threshold can lead to injury to the leg/hoof of the animals. \nFacility immediately corrected this item at the time of the inspection by removing the damaged board. To remain corrected \nfrom this date 4/23/26 forward. \n \nThis inspection and exit briefing were conducted with facility representatives.  \n \n*END OF REPORT* \n \n n",
